:R-HSA-418885  a            obo:GO_0008150 , owl:NamedIndividual ;
        rdfs:comment        "The DCC family includes DCC and neogenin in vertebrates. DCC is required for netrin-induced axon attraction. DCC is a transmembrane protein lacking any identifiable catalytic activity. Protein tyrosine kinase 2/FAK and src family kinases bind constitutively to the cytoplasmic domain of DCC and their activation couples to downstream intracellular signaling complex that directs the organization of actin." ;
        rdfs:label          "DCC mediated attractive signaling" ;
        dc:contributor      "Edited: Garapati, P V, 2008-07-30 10:24:23" , "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Authored: Garapati, P V, 2008-07-16 14:42:16" , "Reviewed: Cooper, HM, 2010-02-16" ;
